This paper deals with the problem of adversarial attacks on machine learning algorithms, which is a topic that is commonly studied in the sub-field of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also makes use of concepts from optimal transport theory, which is a topic that falls under information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper applies its findings to image classification datasets such as CIFAR-10 and MNIST, which are commonly studied in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a novel coupling strategy, which is a technique that is commonly used in optimization and machine learning (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the security implications of adversarial attacks, which is a topic that falls under computer security (cs.CR).
